<worksheet >
  <title>BF-4 Transformations and Combinations</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both problems to earn M. Complete problem 1 and two parts of problem 2 to earn P</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
        <introduction><p>Given the function <m>g(x)=\frac{1}{2}f(x+5)-3</m></p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p>Describe the transformations applied to the function <m>f(x)</m> 
            to get the function <m>g(x)</m>.</p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p>Determine where the point <m>(-4,8)</m> from the graph of 
            <m>f(x)</m> would be shifted to,on the graph of <m>g(x)</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
  <page>
    <title>BF-4 Transformations and Combinations</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both problems to earn M. Complete problem 1 and two parts of problem 2 to earn P</p>
  </introduction>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
        <introduction><p>Given the functions <m>f(x)=\sqrt{2x}</m> and <m>g(x)=x^2+3</m>, find 
            and simplify:</p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p><m>(f+g)(8)</m></p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p><m>(fg)(2)</m></p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p><m>\left(\frac{g}{f}\right)(x)</m></p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p><m>(g\circ f)(x)</m></p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
  </worksheet>